<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3203] We can get an order to open a region while shutting down and it&apos;ll hold up regionserver shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3203</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting and stopping clusters I see that an open directive can come in while we are shutting down all the user space regions on a particular regionserver.  Regionservers will only shut themselves down after all user space regions have closed.  We queue up all the closes at a particular time.  If an open comes in while we are in the closing condition, then the regionserver won&apos;t go down.  The region open needs to be blocked.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
